  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-a65396bc0b49",
  "content": "## Task 8: Factory Function + create_rag_pipeline\n\n    store: Arc<dyn traits::QueryableStore>,\n    engine: Arc<dyn traits::InferenceEngine>,\n    graph: Option<Arc<dyn traits::GraphStore>>,\n    generator: Option<Arc<dyn traits::GenerationEngine>>,\n    config: &CorviaConfig,\n) -> rag_pipeline::RagPipeline {\n    let retriever_: Arc<dyn retriever::Retriever> = match graph {\n        Some(g) => Arc::new(retriever::GraphExpandRetriever::new(\n            store.clone(), engine.clone(), g, config.rag.graph_alpha,\n        )),\n        None => Arc::new(retriever::VectorRetriever::new(store.clone(), engine.clone())),\n    };\n    let augmenter_: Arc<dyn augmenter::Augmenter> = Arc::new(\n        augmenter::StructuredAugmenter::new(config.rag.system_prompt.clone()),\n    );\n    rag_pipeline::RagPipeline::new(retriever_, augmenter_, generator, config.rag.clone())\n}\n```\n\nAdd a `retriever_name()` accessor to `RagPipeline` in `rag_pipeline.rs`:\n\n```rust\n    /// Get the name of the active retriever (for config verification / tests).\n    pub fn retriever_name(&self) -> &str {\n        self.retriever.name()\n    }\n```\n\nAdd necessary imports to `lib.rs`:\n\n```rust\nuse std::sync::Arc;\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- tests::test_create_rag_pipeline --nocapture`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_pipeline.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): create_rag_pipeline factory — auto-selects retriever from capabilities\"\n```\n\n---\n",
